data.text:
The Cisco 9971 IP Phone is an executive class collaboration endpoint that provides high-quality voice and video. It features Gigabit Ethernet, wideband audio, color touchscreen display, built-in Wi-Fi connectivity, and Bluetooth support.

Cisco 9971 Features

Large backlit, high-resolution 640 x 480 pixel, adjustable color display

6 feature buttons with status LEDs

6 call session buttons with status LEDs

4-way navigation cluster

Supports optional Cisco Unified IP Camera for enabling 2-way video calling (sold separately; see drop down option above)

RJ9 headset port for wired analog headsets

2 USB ports for use with accessories such as the Cisco Unified IP Camera and wired and wireless headsets

Bluetooth 2.0 headset profiles add freedom at the desk

High-definition voice (HD voice) provides greater clarity in communications

Supports up to 3 Cisco Unified IP Color Key Expansion Modules

XML applications transform business processes and enhance user experience.

Dual port Gigabit Ethernet switch accomodates collocated PC

Built-in Wi-Fi support (802.11a/b/g)

Powered via 802.3af Power over Ethernet, PoE injector, or Cisco Power Cube 4 (sold separately; see drop down option above)

Supports SIP protocol for signaling; H.264 for video

Compatibility

Supported in Cisco Unified Communications Manager 7.1(3a)SU1 or later

Survivable Remote Site Telephony (SRST) 4.3 or later

CME 8.6 or later
